values: it's been six months since i've even thought of live journal. then all of a sudden...i thought...hey....i have a live journal. fancy that.
TONIGHT.....7:00 P.M......B DUBS.....GILBERT AND WARNER.....PARTY HATS.......HOT WINGS....COOL BATHROOMS W/ T.V.S......YUMMY YUMMY YUMMY.....MORMON CORNER BE THERE OR BE SQUARED.....

ATTENTION ATTENTION...EHHHH HEEEM.....k so this is to the old gang that stood in the corner before school at hamilton. aka "the mormon corner." everyone who stood in that corner is hereby asked to attend a reunion at buffalo wild wings on TUESDAY THE 26TH OF JULY. if you dont come....you're just silly. everyone is moving away and it's kinda sad so me and arnold decided it would be a good idea to kick off life with a bang. and i dont want to hear any sorry excuses like..."oh i dont like so and so and they might be there." because we are not in high school anymore. we are big kids now and should act like it. so be there or be a pumpkin!!!

summer vacation is greater than great so far.  me and my family spent a week at a ski resort in the middle of the mountains. snowbird is home of the 2nd tallest rock wall in the WORLD and i climbed all 120 ft. of it. they also had a huge slide going down the mountain. i raced my brother in law down on a toboggan and kicked his wimpy butt. it left him with burns all over his arms and legs. yay. the zip line was pretty cool too. it was reeeeally tall. then we went up a tram to the top of the mountains and built a snowman...in july!!!! then me and my cousins went to temple square and met up w/ my famous friend josh and saw lots of old men in purple suits. later that night we went to a giant institute party that josh's band was playing at. there must have been at least two or three hundred people there. i've never been a friend of the band's before so it was pretty tight. it was almost like i was famous!!!!! and that is where i met the boy of my dreams.....and this is where the story ends....oh and i drove josh's motorcycle!!!!!!!! it was a super trip...

what...... excuse me.....something smells stupid.... my parents are out of town and i'm getting home before curfew every night. that cant be right. someone please tell me how to be a rebel.    BUT.....BUT.....much good has come of this week. jill has introduced me to some pretty quality movies while i've been staying at her house. 1st there was white chicks. i dont think i've laughed so hard watching a movie by myself. i woke up the entire house w/ my laughter. then there was drop dead gorgeous. same thing w/ the laughing and the having a good time was had w/ that one too. then there was garden state. ehh..not even that good. but.....the point is.....

writing on live journal just about every day....a sure sign summer has begun...
i'm going to be home alone for a week. my parents are leaving tomorrow night and i just found out tonight. they are leaving me w/ nothing..... so if you see me rummaging through your trash can or sleeping in your gutters...you will know why. what if the bad guys get me??
ever feel like God gets bored and decides to see how awkward he can make your life for a short period of time?
i have an interview for wells fargo tomorrow.....i'm shaking in my boots....

you know that floating glittery feeling you get right after you watch a chick flick? it's like everything is going to be okay.....i am happy. i wish i could just freeze time and always feel this way. today i found out my sister isnt mormon anymore and i guess she hasnt been for about a year now. that breaks my heart cuz i know she isnt happy with life. she thinks she is making her life better but she's not. she is always stressed out, tired, unsociable, and hiding from everything. you cant be happy in life if you are hiding from life. i just want to hit her over the head w/ a hammer and make her realize what she is missing out on. i know you cant force someone to believe a certain way or think a certain way but when you love someone so much you only want the best for them. i just wish she thought she deserved the best. i wish i could do more.

so california was awesome. i got to do everything i wanted to and had an abundance of fun! disneyland showed me a side i never saw in him before. oooh was it magical. just thinking about it gives me the goose bumps. its up  there w/ seeing a mother breast feed her child in the line for the peter pan ride. :/ by gosh woman there are children present!!!  this trip taught me a lesson i actually understand now. people are always going to think i suck at life; that i am evil and out to get them. well all i can say to that is i try not to suck at life and i dont think i'm any worse at it than anyone else. second i dont think i'm evil. so instead of worrying my pretty little head about uh oh who hates me now, and oh no what did i do wrong this time, i am going to live my life the way i want and be who i want to be. i'm sorry if this ruins any ones plans but the cookie must crumble some time so try your best to get over it. everyone should watch the movie Eternal Sunshine. that movie inspired me. the moral of the story is to let go of the little things. dont let the petty things stop you from enjoying the beautiful things in life. just imagine not freaking out for once. imagine not being offended and just letting it go. imagine giving some one the benefit of the doubt or even a second chance. just imagine how much happier life would be. well it's just a theory. take it or leave it i guess. :)

uuugghhh its too bad i have to go to california tomorrow. just think of all the dreadfull things i'll have to do while i'm up there. meet cute boys, go to the beach, meet cute boys, ride roller coasters, meet cute boys,   go shopping, meet cute boys....ugggh such a rough life.

oh i wonder wonder what's in a wonder ball. man alive! what a wonderful summmer. just smell it. go on, take a whiff. its beautiful!! i'm never going to school again!!! bwa hahahaha!! well at least not for a few more months. this summer is gunna rock the shack! i'm going on 2 california trips w/ my friends, count them 2!! then i'm going to the bright eyes concert, then utah for a week! its gunna be the best summer EVA!!
just to let all my mexican food lovers know....there are about 5 bags of extra seranos food at my house left over from the wedding. so in the words of bill and ted....party on dudes!!!

today i had a wonderful brunch w/ the governor. we had tea and crumpets and talked about out mother -in-laws. the governor keeps trying to convince me to run for president!! can you believe that silly old man? oh how i will miss and reminisce the grand ol' times i have spent w/ that man.

so this cute little old guy came up to me while i was sitting on the curb waiting for a ride and asked me what i was thinking about. i told him to eat bugars and that it was none of his business. i didnt really but wouldnt that be funny? i really said, "not much." he then replied, "boyfriend?" i said, "nope." he said, "school?" i said, "nope. just everything." then he said, "i love those times." he then apologized for interrupting me. i thought he was a silly man but then i thought about it. it really is good to sit and think. think about life. i dont do it as often as i should. so i sat and pondered and i came to the conclusion that i am lame to people a lot. i just want to apologize to anyone i have been lame to. it's true. i really dont mean to. most of the time i just dont think. so i'm sorry. and i really mean no harm. just tell me when i'm being lame. i really do need it and appreciate it.

hey all lets make a coke a cola commercial this summer with everyone. it would be so classic.
pleeeeese....
i want to say i suck at life but that would be saying too little atm.

i need more life in my life. like today for instance. today was a delightful satisfying day. i got much happiness accomplished. richard was awesome for treating me and jacob to RICHARD'S FUN FILLED DAY OF HAPPINESS. that's what i named it. he bought us food and took us to the diamond backs game. it was freakin awesome. richard and jacob hid 3 drinks and a bunch of candy in their pockets and i was the decoy! it was sweet! i felt like a true FBI agent. if only everyone had a friend like richard the world would be a happier place. jacob's pretty tight too.

crazy things. hmmmm... well tonight i thought of the time me and melissa and my sister and her friend walked around her neighborhood at 11:30 at night. we heard a band playing in someones house so we decided to join the party. i think it was a work party or something cuz it was all adults. they didnt seem to think it was too wierd that 4 teenage girls were at the party so we got front row seets on the couch to watch the band. some people already heard that one so i will think of another one.      so then there was the time that  me and melissa spent the day as bums in a shopping cart. we  took turns pushing eachother  around town in this shopping cart, making trouble every where we went. the furnature  store was the best. we stayed there  for at least an hour taking naps on the show room beds and playing an intense game of chess. we even had one of the  workers coaching us on playing tips. i miss being immature.

I think it's really funny when people pull hats and beanies off each other's heads. I think it's the best game ever. I really appreciate especially when people run away with my beanie after pulling it off, then laughs at my messed up hair. That right there is actually why the hat was invented. They are just asking someone to pull it right off their head to expose their hat hair. So if ever you see someone wearing a hat, ya-mica, turban, etc., you just pull that sucker right off their head. Trust me, they'll absolutely love you for it!
i decided i wanted the big huge colorful something for myself. So this is the answer to the big question as to "what the heck is going on": people are simply confused.
the first person who can tell me what the heck is going on gets a big huge colorful something.

so...second day of school could have gone just a little bit more exciting maybe. time went by so slowly no matter what i was doing. i know i should feel blessed to have half days...but i still have a problem with something. WHY DO TEACHERS HAVE TO FREAKING TEACH ALL THE TIME? cant they just sit there and say..."here's a fantastic movie class. feel free to snack on these delicious appetizers and take a nap if you start to get drowsy. dont worry about homework. homework is for nerds." that is what teachers SHOULD do. but no. they stand there....and talk...for hours. and some days, they even expect you to sit there and listen to them continue to talk during conference hour like thats what's on everyone's mind. they dont even care that I lose all feeling in both butt cheeks by conference time. The only thing i could think about while trying to look like i was listening, was how tired their feet must be standing. i just wanted to throw a big rock at their knee caps and MAKE them sit. AND STOP TALKING. AND STOP GIVING ME INFORMATION AND SILLY RULES AND TRYING TO BE FUNNY. it must be so exhausting being a teacher. you'd think they'd just ask for a break. but they never break. not even if you throw rocks st them. ooh! just a side note:being bluntly honest with people usually results in not good feelings towards that person. so it's a good idea to stay clear of it. haha mr, minafri started singing "jesus loves me yes he does...." really quietly today in class. that man is a mad man!

it seems like we just barely started our senior year. now it's halfway over!! then i think about how it seems like i just barely got to know all of you, and after high school i probably wont ever see some of you again!!! that's so sad. :(

heyus! i'm sooooo going snowboarding! i dont know how it will go but i'm sure i will be coming home thursday with several bruises on my buttocks. i am also at a turning point in my life. maybe its the christmasness in the air or maybe it was something in the egg nog my mom made. i dont know who cares to know but pretty much, i'm sick of sucking at life. Therefore, starting now i am saving for a car(for real), excercising, eating right, sleeping right, applying for asu, saving for a place to stay after high school, and in march i will get a new job that i actually like. wish me luck as i feed myself to the sharks.
there's nothing better than watching old movies by yourself at 1 a.m.

- my ride came and i was greeted w/ chocolate cake and hot chocolate made by the lovely        richard.

- spilled hot chocolate on myself and was late for zero hour.

- got sick and pissed off during 5th hour and ended up yelling at these kids who ratted me out for ditching.

- went to lunch, and saw richard's precious puppys 

- i told the puppy to pee on the seminary carpet and ofcoarse it did and so i got to clean it up.

- went home and watched a movie by myself and took a nap.

- made plans, had to brake plans, made better plans, had to brake those plans, then had those plans broken; all for what? to satisfy the fast food needs of two boys who wanted to get back to their virtual reality.
i want to go to the fish store this week and buy myself an angel fish to replace my dead friend Eeeeww. I will call her....Butterfly.
i could never ever be a doctor, a mortician, or a transy. they are all discusting jobs.

ARMED AND DANGEROUS and she is waiting to GET you too. she'll make you laugh at her "i can say whatever i want to say" personality. but be careful when you laugh, because these are not the good kind of laughing pains she'll leave you w/.   nnnNO. she stabs you w/ her cold cold COLD-hearted spear as she takes from you the most important thing you own: your divine right of superiority over those who are younger than you. i'm only telling you this for your own well-being. it's hard to sleep when you are hungry, but it's even harder to eat when you're too tired. i'm screwed.

ty your shoes and jacob jingle hymer shmit were my heroes today at buffalo wild wings. they did the unspeakable 12 suicide wings in 2 minutes. that's just crazy. and they did it w/ only a few tears. so today i was picking through a few different hobbies i could start up and i couldn't decide so i picked 5. they are as follows:                                    

1) becoming tite friends w/ one of the security guards at hamilton during my aiding class. i will soon know when their birthday is, what they want for their birthday, and what their most traumatic birthday experience has been.
2) learning how to gleak across the room.
3) altering my personality to where it becomes acceptable for me to say, "Oh H' no cracka. you get off this shiz for i call yem occifers on yall to bust a caps on yalls motha for this harrismint!"
4) learning the art of total peace and tranquility.
5) finding what is equivilent to halo 2 in a girl's perspective.

a word to those who want to keep thier best friends....learn thier birthdays!!!!!

havent updated in quite some time so you all can skim through my exciting day!!  i felt like the most pathetic person today cuz everyone was freaking out about the deformities on my arm. first the vice principal freaked about it and told me to go to the nurse, then both the nurses were poking at them and told me i had to call my mom and make a doctor's apt, then she comes an hour later from work and takes me out of school like it needed to be done in a rush, or even looked at at all. the doctor wanted to give me a shot but i said heck no. so she gave me cream and pills for my extreme condition. i wanted to steal some rubber gloves from the doctor and make utters but my mom wouldnt let me. i dont know why people always think they have to talk quietly in the doctor's office. my mom kept whispering and i asked her why. she said because it's fun and mysterious?? now i know why i say dumb things.

whoever answers this riddle gets a prize....i'm a bum, and i need something in my life. something worth-while. something special i suppose! i need something really really good to make me super happy and make me feel like i'm doing something productive w/ my life. it should probably smell like vanilla and be as fun as water skiing, w/ out the sunburn. yes, it should be similar to water skiing AND getting a great tan (no sunburn), WHILE smelling like vanilla. SO.. something to that effect and you will get a prize if it's good enough.

today hat day...."eehh, ok".                              Tomorrow wig day??  "yessssssssssssss"
              so i was trying on a few wigs for tomorrow's school spirit day. Success! I found THE perfect wig. it's so real looking and yet so....well.... hilarious that you will most likely pee your pants when i sport my new do tomorrow. I'm just warning you all so you can bring an extra pair of pantilones', or "chonies" as the native americans like to call them. i wish my hair actually looked like this. it is so low maintenance and very striking. i feel so lively, perky, and young-spirited!! now i am going to frolic through a meadow!

Staying home from school used to be like running away from home. Now it's just like sleeping in. If that makes sense.  
          Speaking of sleeping in, i slept in til almost 12 today. oh man that was Gooooooood. i mean, it was so good that it was better than sitting on top of the roof watching fireworks on the 4th of july. better than waking up on a saturday morning at 5:30 when you are 6 years old just to watch Dennis the Menace. Better than the time i died and went to heaven.

i was in a very chipper mood today, despite only getting 3 1/2 hours of sleep last night. i was in a hug mood too and Brother Clamtonite the seminary teacher looked like he needed a hug so i tried to give him one but he freaked out on me. I would even say he went nuts! I dont think he appriciated it very much. I dont think i'll try that again. But anyway, today was a good day overall becuase it went by way fast. I love my first hour! the lady gives me a treat everyday and acts like i save her life everytime i do something for her. it's the best class ever! i got to give a tour of the school to this new girl today and she seemed really nice. oh what it is to be the new kid. *sigh.....*

oh man, this morning i went to leisures picture place to pick out my senior pictures and me and my mom had some good laughs. in all my pics it looks like i was looking at something naked and trying to to keep a straight face. hmm yeah so re-takes were re-scheduled for goodness sakes. but i dont know where my black shirt is anymore.  geez. so much drama is going on right now. i wish it would all stop. even at little caesars. it's all the same. i'm trying to stay out of it but it follows me every where i go. i hate drama. HATE IT! becuase it's dumb. i really couldnt care less if amanda and linsey both like jeremy at work becuase we all know that jeremy is gay.  they are just waisting their time backstabbing eachother for this guy because even if jeremy does pick one of the girls, they will go out for a while, share some good times, then he will wake up one morning and decide that he doesnt like that girl anymore, then he wont tell her, but instead decide to stop talking to her, then not tell her why he isnt talking to her, then he will make her find out from one of his friends since he is too pansy to have an adult conversation about it to her face. and THAT'S how it all ends. so good luck amanda and linsey!

man it is really hot outside. i mean...really hot. especially when you are stuck out there for 2 hours. now i know how the sun must feel. it is around it's self all the time. that would be horrible!       i went shopping at walgreens w/ cool kid tony and i almost bought the bossest sunglasses. i was afraid they would make me too cool though so i had to pass. peath out.

so i was sitting in seminary after school and i had a long non-productive talk w/ Bro. Clanton, the new seminary teacher.  i am still trying to understand his reasoning for the way he conducts his teaching. It's like he doesnt even care if his students like him. (Or maybe he does but he isnt succeeding if that was his intention.) it made me realize that i need to stop asking why people are the way they are and just except the fact that some people will just confuse the crack out of me no matter how hard i try to understand their intentions and reasons.
